WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.100
Look, all I'm saying is,
if they're going to go to the trouble

00:02.166 --> 00:03.667
of remaking a classic movie...

00:03.734 --> 00:06.300
I agree with you. They should've
at least used real apes.

00:06.367 --> 00:08.967
[GASPS] Oh, good, Lizzie, you're here.
You almost missed it.

00:09.033 --> 00:10.133
Almost missed what?

00:10.200 --> 00:12.400
Ethan Craft. He's... he's...

00:12.467 --> 00:14.133
Uh, is today the day?

00:14.200 --> 00:15.967
Is this, like, one of those
girl things that

00:16.033 --> 00:18.033
I'm not going to get?
Or even care about?

00:18.100 --> 00:19.467
Actually, it's an Ethan thing.

00:19.533 --> 00:21.967
It's a known fact that
all the boys in Ethan's family

00:22.033 --> 00:24.066
get dirt bikes when they're 14.

00:24.133 --> 00:25.133
So what?

00:25.200 --> 00:27.734
So... So look at him.

00:41.967 --> 00:43.834
Oh, to be that helmet.

00:44.567 --> 00:45.734
Ladies...

00:47.000 --> 00:50.600
Oh... He's more...
something than usual.

00:50.700 --> 00:52.767
He is. He so is.

00:52.834 --> 00:55.166
It's like he's Ethan, only more.

00:55.233 --> 00:56.567
-And better.
-LIZZIE: Yeah.

00:57.433 --> 00:59.266
Okay, what am I missing here?

00:59.333 --> 01:02.266
Excuse me. Pardon me.
Hot coffee. Coming through.

01:02.333 --> 01:04.266
I don't see any coffee.

01:04.333 --> 01:06.667
No, but the expression
parts a crowd like Moses.

01:06.734 --> 01:08.200
So what's all the hubbub?

01:08.266 --> 01:10.700
-Oh, it's Ethan.
-He's all grown up.

01:11.533 --> 01:12.767
Oh, yeah.

01:13.767 --> 01:16.934
Larry, why are there teeny bits
of tissue all over your face?

01:17.333 --> 01:20.000
-I started shaving.
-[MOUTHING] What?

01:20.867 --> 01:22.667
This isn't a one-man-town, you know.

01:22.734 --> 01:24.166
There's plenty of room
for the both of us.

01:24.233 --> 01:25.767
-Oh, and you, too, Gordo.
-Huh?

01:26.333 --> 01:27.400
Uh, nothing.

01:28.033 --> 01:30.633
<i>Hasta luego.</i> May the force
be with you. And peace out.

01:30.700 --> 01:31.767
[SNIFFLES]

01:31.934 --> 01:34.000
I don't get it.
Tudgeman starts shaving

01:34.066 --> 01:35.667
and suddenly he thinks he's all that.

01:35.734 --> 01:37.734
It does kind of mean something, Gordo.

01:37.800 --> 01:39.734
What, that he can raid
his father's medicine cabinet?

01:42.367 --> 01:44.600
Gordo, shaving is a sign of maturity.

01:44.867 --> 01:47.100
Maturity? It's Tudgeman.

01:47.166 --> 01:48.934
I don't know.
Must be something in the water.

01:49.000 --> 01:50.467
I mean, first Ethan, now Lar...

01:50.533 --> 01:52.066
Oh, you're not actually going to use

01:52.133 --> 01:54.467
Ethan and Larry
in the same sentence, are you?

01:54.533 --> 01:55.934
You just did.

01:56.467 --> 01:58.900
Look, Gordo, maybe they're...

01:58.967 --> 02:02.100
[CHUCKLING] You know, growing up
a little faster than you are.

02:02.166 --> 02:03.166
[INHALES]

02:04.900 --> 02:06.300
[INHALES]

02:06.367 --> 02:08.800
I... I don't even know
how to respond to that.

02:11.166 --> 02:15.367
At last, after years of conversation,
I finally stumped him!

02:16.800 --> 02:19.934
Look, Gordo, don't worry.
I-I'm sure you'll start shaving.

02:20.567 --> 02:21.567
Someday.

02:21.700 --> 02:24.300
[CHUCKLES] Come on, let's go see
what Ethan looks like up close.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.400
[GIGGLING]

02:28.734 --> 02:30.166
Not even a good-bye?

02:30.233 --> 02:32.400
[THEME SONG PLAYING]

03:12.033 --> 03:13.800
-Hey, Gordo.
-Elizabeth.

03:15.200 --> 03:16.200
Elizabeth?

03:16.266 --> 03:18.967
My mom doesn't even call me that
when she's mad at me.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.033
The name's Lizzie, David.

03:21.100 --> 03:23.400
And how are you
this fine afternoon, Miss Sanchez?

03:24.467 --> 03:25.967
Are you feeling okay?

03:26.033 --> 03:27.233
I'm being sophisticated.

03:27.300 --> 03:29.266
Uh, no, you're being annoying.

03:29.633 --> 03:32.934
Yeah, you're right.
I can't even pretend to be a grownup.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.467
I'm going to be
a kid forever, aren't I?

03:35.734 --> 03:37.400
Okay, a little help here.

03:37.467 --> 03:39.834
Gordo's usually the one
with all the answers.

03:40.467 --> 03:42.667
Gordo, look, there are tons
of kids around here.

03:42.734 --> 03:44.834
Yeah, and if there weren't,
it'd be really weird

03:44.900 --> 03:46.734
that we're all still in school.

03:46.800 --> 03:48.100
I just can't believe that my parents

03:48.166 --> 03:50.266
left such a crucial decision
in my hands.

03:50.333 --> 03:51.333
What decision?

03:51.400 --> 03:52.667
When to become a man.

03:53.367 --> 03:54.834
Okay, I'm Jewish, right?

03:54.900 --> 03:56.233
Well, traditionally, in my religion,

03:56.300 --> 03:58.066
when you turn 13,
you have a Bar Mitzvah.

03:58.133 --> 03:59.667
[GASPS] A... A bar?

03:59.734 --> 04:02.433
Like, where you drink
and stuff? At 13?

04:02.500 --> 04:05.033
No, it's a ceremony.
You start it as a child

04:05.100 --> 04:06.600
and when you're finished,
you're a man.

04:06.667 --> 04:08.633
Ooh, that must take
a really long time.

04:08.700 --> 04:11.667
No, only about a half an hour.
You read from the Torah and...

04:11.734 --> 04:13.233
Okay, you lost me again.

04:13.300 --> 04:15.133
It's the Bible, the Jewish version.

04:15.200 --> 04:17.667
So you read from the Torah
and you sing some prayers

04:17.734 --> 04:19.834
and you give a little speech
and then you have this huge party

04:19.900 --> 04:22.066
where they give you tons
of money and gifts and stuff.

04:22.133 --> 04:23.433
People give you money?

04:23.500 --> 04:24.767
And you didn't have one?

04:24.834 --> 04:26.467
Well, my parents didn't push me.

04:26.533 --> 04:28.433
When they were kids,
they didn't have a choice.

04:28.500 --> 04:30.667
They wanted me to come
to the decision on my own.

04:30.734 --> 04:32.367
And now I totally missed the window.

04:33.400 --> 04:36.400
Open up! Open up!
<i>Beaucoup</i> bucks are at stake.

04:36.734 --> 04:38.300
Didn't you want a bar mitzvah?

04:38.367 --> 04:39.767
I guess I didn't see the point.

04:39.834 --> 04:42.400
Like a half hour ceremony
would turn me into a man?

04:42.467 --> 04:44.734
Who cares? We're talking about money.

04:45.567 --> 04:47.033
Maybe you're like Peter Pan.

04:47.800 --> 04:49.400
Doomed to be a boy forever.

04:49.467 --> 04:50.900
[GASPS]
Ooh, clap if you believe.

04:52.033 --> 04:54.300
-Tinker Bell? Hello?
-LIZZIE: Ugh.

04:54.367 --> 04:57.467
Personally, I don't see the big point
in growing up anytime soon.

04:57.533 --> 04:59.700
I mean, we can't drive, we can't vote.

04:59.767 --> 05:01.033
Where are all the perks?

05:01.100 --> 05:04.734
Exactly. And 13, is kind of young
to be considered a grownup.

05:04.800 --> 05:06.734
In my culture, you have to be 15.

05:07.033 --> 05:09.800
We have a ceremony, too.
A <i>Quincea√±era.</i>

05:09.867 --> 05:11.166
Ooh, do they give you money?

05:11.567 --> 05:14.066
I'm not sure but lots of music
and great food, though.

05:14.133 --> 05:15.800
Speaking of which, I'm starved.

05:15.867 --> 05:17.834
That's always a good sign
that you're feeling better.

05:17.900 --> 05:20.100
Please, I think about food constantly.

05:20.166 --> 05:21.100
Me, too.

05:22.333 --> 05:25.834
Food, bringing people
together everywhere. <i>L'chaim.</i>

05:26.500 --> 05:27.767
[DOORBELL RINGS]

05:29.633 --> 05:30.767
JO AND SAM: I'll get it.

05:32.667 --> 05:34.100
-Hey, handsome.
-Hey...

05:35.800 --> 05:37.667
-There, beautiful.
-That's better.

05:38.600 --> 05:42.467
Hey, Mrs. Robinson.
Matt, what did you do this time?

05:42.533 --> 05:44.200
It's all a misunderstanding.

05:44.266 --> 05:47.133
He was stealing oranges
from my tree, again.

05:47.834 --> 05:49.033
Is this true, Matt?

05:49.100 --> 05:53.000
Well, "stealing"
is such a... strong word.

05:53.066 --> 05:54.500
Get in the house right now.

05:55.800 --> 05:58.233
It's the third time this week.

05:58.300 --> 05:59.300
Fourth.

06:00.367 --> 06:01.400
Oh.

06:01.834 --> 06:05.633
Fourth time this week that
he climbed into my garden,

06:05.700 --> 06:07.667
crushed my rhododendrons,

06:07.734 --> 06:09.867
and took that which
did not belong to him.

06:09.934 --> 06:11.166
It's criminal!

06:11.233 --> 06:13.567
I'm very sorry,
and it won't happen again.

06:13.633 --> 06:15.166
That's what you said yesterday.

06:15.233 --> 06:17.867
Boys will be boys, huh, Mrs. Robinson?

06:19.367 --> 06:22.400
Thank you. We will take care
of it, Mrs. Robinson.

06:27.500 --> 06:29.200
"Boys will be boys?"

06:29.266 --> 06:30.500
What's the big deal?

06:30.567 --> 06:33.633
I mean, she's got about
a million oranges on her tree.

06:33.700 --> 06:36.800
So I sold two maybe
three... dozen.

06:37.200 --> 06:38.200
You did?

06:38.266 --> 06:39.400
You did what?

06:39.700 --> 06:41.467
Hey, I would've split
the profits with her

06:41.533 --> 06:45.033
but she seemed so angry.

06:45.100 --> 06:46.333
Can you blame her?

06:46.767 --> 06:47.834
Can you?

06:48.567 --> 06:50.734
He said he was going
to split the profits with her.

06:50.800 --> 06:51.800
Sam!

06:53.433 --> 06:55.000
Don't steal oranges.

06:55.066 --> 06:56.967
-Okay.
-See? All better.

06:57.066 --> 06:59.433
That's it? That's all
you're going to do about it?

06:59.533 --> 07:01.533
Yes? No?

07:01.600 --> 07:02.600
Maybe?

07:03.633 --> 07:04.900
What was the question again?

07:04.967 --> 07:06.800
I don't believe this.

07:06.867 --> 07:08.767
It's like I have two boys
to discipline.

07:08.834 --> 07:10.033
Can I be excused?

07:10.100 --> 07:11.967
This stuff is getting kind of heavy.

07:12.066 --> 07:14.633
Sure. You're excused.
'Cause you know what?

07:15.233 --> 07:16.700
I'm going on strike.

07:17.433 --> 07:19.633
From now on, you're in charge, Dad.

07:19.700 --> 07:20.767
Cool!

07:20.834 --> 07:23.367
Yeah, when Matt's school calls,
which they will,

07:23.433 --> 07:25.700
when the neighbors complain,
which they will,

07:25.767 --> 07:27.200
when Lizzie screams "Mom!"

07:27.266 --> 07:30.900
which she definitely will,
take those as your cues.

07:30.900 --> 07:32.367
'Cause they're all yours.

07:32.467 --> 07:34.100
-Yeah, but...
-And if you need me,

07:34.166 --> 07:35.967
I'll be soaking in the tub.

07:38.600 --> 07:41.367
Guess it's just me
and you, Pops. Orange?

07:42.000 --> 07:43.533
-Thanks.
-Later.

07:47.166 --> 07:48.433
Ooh.

07:48.500 --> 07:50.133
-Hey, guess what?
-What?

07:50.200 --> 07:51.934
You know how I was
bummed out yesterday about

07:52.000 --> 07:55.133
the whole ceremonial-rites-of
-passage-growing-up-being-a-man thing?

07:55.200 --> 07:57.000
[SNORTS]
No, what are you talking about?

07:57.066 --> 07:58.233
Come on, this is serious.

07:58.667 --> 08:01.433
Really serious.
He didn't even get my sarcasm.

08:02.233 --> 08:03.333
Sorry, go ahead.

08:03.400 --> 08:05.266
Well, after school,
I went on this quest.

08:05.333 --> 08:08.033
I wanted to see how my brothers
in the adult world became men.

08:08.100 --> 08:09.600
You have brothers?

08:10.033 --> 08:12.967
I mean in the philosophical sense.
I spoke to a bunch of guys.

08:13.033 --> 08:14.266
You know, interviewed them.

08:14.333 --> 08:17.166
It was very enlightening.
I even recorded it for posterity.

08:17.233 --> 08:18.367
Ooh, can we see?

08:19.767 --> 08:21.100
After high school.

08:22.567 --> 08:26.600
I needed some direction, some purpose.

08:26.667 --> 08:27.667
GORDO: So what'd you do?

08:28.200 --> 08:30.767
And I asked my father
for a driving lesson.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.900
We painted our faces
for the Super Bowl.

08:34.300 --> 08:36.633
I was blue. He was orange.

08:36.700 --> 08:38.800
-Da' Bears!
-Da' Bears!

08:39.400 --> 08:41.767
One day, my father
took me to the lake.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.400
He said, "Son,

08:45.967 --> 08:48.567
"today you will catch your first fish.

08:49.333 --> 08:53.200
"And in so doing,
today you will become a man."

08:53.266 --> 08:55.600
-GORDO: How old were you?
-I was 16.

08:55.967 --> 08:57.266
Fifteen and a half.

08:57.333 --> 08:58.367
Eleven.

08:58.433 --> 08:59.533
BOTH: Seventeen.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.600
Eighteen when I met Miranda's mother.

09:02.633 --> 09:04.567
That is the day I became a man.

09:04.633 --> 09:06.333
Uh, my first tattoo.

09:06.633 --> 09:08.834
I caught it with my bare hands.

09:09.166 --> 09:11.700
Never has a fish tasted so good.

09:11.767 --> 09:14.500
Or the way Walter Payton cried
when they won the game.

09:15.867 --> 09:17.467
It was a beautiful thing.

09:17.533 --> 09:21.200
Yeah, because they were
man enough to be that way

09:21.266 --> 09:23.300
in front of millions of people.

09:23.367 --> 09:26.800
Plus, the chicks really dig 'em.
[CHUCKLES]

09:26.934 --> 09:29.900
Anyway, I paid for the light pole so,

09:29.967 --> 09:32.533
you know, it was a lesson
in responsibility.

09:33.333 --> 09:36.867
And that pretty much
was when I became a man.

09:37.834 --> 09:39.533
I now know what I need to do.

09:39.600 --> 09:41.300
Are you going to say tattoo parlor?

09:41.367 --> 09:44.200
That's so gross. I'm so there.

09:44.266 --> 09:46.000
I can always count on you, Miranda.

09:46.567 --> 09:47.867
You guys are not serious.

09:47.934 --> 09:51.600
You're right. I'm Gordo.
I'm about to become a man.

09:54.266 --> 09:56.266
[TATTOO NEEDLE BUZZING]

10:24.467 --> 10:27.934
All I'm saying is, I thought
the tattoo of the flower was pretty.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.900
Not exactly manly, but...

10:29.967 --> 10:31.800
Well, apparently, neither am I.

10:31.867 --> 10:34.700
Look, Gordo, one of the great things
about you

10:34.767 --> 10:36.633
is you do things on your own time

10:36.700 --> 10:38.200
not when everybody else does.

10:38.266 --> 10:40.300
Yeah, what's the big rush
in growing up anyway?

10:40.367 --> 10:42.200
I just want to know when it happens.

10:42.266 --> 10:44.033
I mean, where's my moment?

10:44.100 --> 10:46.333
I can't shave yet,
I don't have a dirt bike.

10:46.400 --> 10:48.767
The tattoo was obviously not for me.

10:48.834 --> 10:50.667
I can't even catch a fish.

10:50.767 --> 10:52.834
How am I going to know
when I'm no longer a boy?

10:53.233 --> 10:54.800
I guess you'll just know.

10:54.867 --> 10:56.033
That's not good enough.

10:56.100 --> 10:59.367
You guys will know
when it happens. It's biological.

10:59.433 --> 11:02.100
Ooh, creepy. Let's not go there.

11:02.166 --> 11:04.033
Never mind. I guess it's a guy thing.

11:04.100 --> 11:05.433
You guys just can't understand.

11:05.934 --> 11:07.934
Gordo, we're trying to understand.

11:08.500 --> 11:11.734
I'd better go.
It's getting near my bedtime anyway.

11:17.200 --> 11:19.100
That was a joke. I may still be a kid,

11:19.166 --> 11:21.033
but I don't actually have a bedtime.

11:21.300 --> 11:23.300
-[SCOFFS] We knew that.
-Okay.

11:25.467 --> 11:26.467
I didn't.

11:26.800 --> 11:29.633
What's his rush? Girls mature
faster than boys anyway.

11:30.433 --> 11:33.667
Hey! That means me first. Me! Me! Me!

11:35.467 --> 11:36.567
-Matt...
-[VIDEO GAME NOISES]

11:38.567 --> 11:40.633
I thought we said
no more video games.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.934
It's part of
your punishment, remember?

11:43.000 --> 11:44.700
I thought that was yesterday.

11:44.767 --> 11:47.500
You said that painting
Mr. Nelson's lawn green

11:47.567 --> 11:49.700
was an improvement over
the dead grass and weeds

11:49.767 --> 11:51.100
that usually grow there.

11:51.166 --> 11:53.200
And you were punishing me to,

11:53.266 --> 11:55.834
I think you said "prove a point."

11:56.333 --> 11:57.667
He's just joking, honey.

11:58.800 --> 12:01.133
Oh, I'm sorry, I wasn't listening.
Were you guys talking?

12:06.900 --> 12:09.166
You just got yourself three weeks
of kitchen cleanup, mister.

12:09.233 --> 12:11.133
What? What for?

12:11.200 --> 12:12.834
For making me look bad
in front of mom.

12:13.867 --> 12:15.200
That's so unfair.

12:15.266 --> 12:16.433
-Is not.
-Is, too.

12:16.500 --> 12:17.867
-Is not.
-Is, too.

12:17.934 --> 12:19.000
Is not.

12:30.567 --> 12:31.633
Sam!

13:03.800 --> 13:04.834
[DOG BARKS]

13:06.867 --> 13:08.700
[DOG WHIMPERS]

13:11.133 --> 13:15.233
Your behavior your attitude,
are just so... bad.

13:15.700 --> 13:18.900
I really... I don't know what
I'm going to do with you, Matt.

13:18.967 --> 13:22.066
Be Zen-like. Do nothing.

13:22.133 --> 13:23.133
[SNORTS]

13:23.200 --> 13:25.467
That is exactly
the attitude I'm talking about.

13:25.533 --> 13:27.333
What would your mother do
in this situation?

13:27.467 --> 13:29.734
What is the situation exactly?

13:29.800 --> 13:33.033
Well, you put our garden hose
in the Lippins' mailbox.

13:33.100 --> 13:35.166
You decided you wanted
to play "mudslinger"

13:35.233 --> 13:37.533
in the Dennises' yard,
and you gave Cocoa a mohawk.

13:37.600 --> 13:41.300
Hey, it was hot outside.
I thought I was doing Cocoa a favor.

13:41.367 --> 13:43.467
All right, that's it,
go to your room.

13:43.533 --> 13:45.200
-My room?
-Yes.

13:45.266 --> 13:47.767
That's it? That's my punishment?

13:47.834 --> 13:49.300
Hey, I'm just getting started.

13:49.367 --> 13:52.100
Okay, so... When do you think
you'll be finished, then?

13:52.400 --> 13:53.834
That's it. Go!

13:54.667 --> 13:56.700
Amateur. Total amateur.

13:57.133 --> 13:58.633
Just go.

14:00.333 --> 14:01.400
[SIGHS]

14:01.467 --> 14:02.467
Hi, honey.

14:02.533 --> 14:03.533
[SCOFFS]

14:04.133 --> 14:05.834
Uh, Mom, can I talk to you
about something? It's...

14:05.900 --> 14:07.533
Sorry, I'm off-duty. Sam?

14:07.600 --> 14:09.567
Maybe you're better at this
than at disciplining.

14:10.867 --> 14:12.033
[SIGHS]

14:14.433 --> 14:16.467
So... [SIGHS] What's up?

14:18.333 --> 14:20.500
Yeah. Like I'm really going
to talk to my dad

14:20.567 --> 14:22.200
about what's going on in my life.

14:23.100 --> 14:24.133
Everything okay?

14:24.433 --> 14:25.433
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

14:25.667 --> 14:27.200
Well, when he asks so nicely.

14:27.734 --> 14:29.900
Yeah. I saw you in Gordo's movie.

14:29.967 --> 14:32.133
Oh, yeah? That come out okay?

14:32.200 --> 14:34.700
Pretty good. Gordo still feels
like a kid, though.

14:34.900 --> 14:36.166
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

14:36.233 --> 14:38.967
Yeah. I remember what that feels like.

14:39.900 --> 14:42.100
It feels... light.

14:43.533 --> 14:46.467
Light? I knew we didn't speak
the same language.

14:47.233 --> 14:49.133
You know, like eating
an ice cream cone

14:49.200 --> 14:51.000
and it's dripping down
the side of your hand.

14:51.500 --> 14:52.900
Or you're playing baseball
in the street

14:52.967 --> 14:54.166
and the sun's about to set.

14:54.266 --> 14:57.567
Or staying up late
just because it's fun.

14:57.734 --> 14:59.600
[CHUCKLES]
Why else would you stay up late?

14:59.667 --> 15:00.934
[LAUGHS]

15:01.133 --> 15:03.066
Because it's the only time
you have to eat your dinner.

15:04.200 --> 15:06.834
Or pay your bills. Or do your laundry.

15:07.767 --> 15:08.800
Oh...

15:08.867 --> 15:11.667
But it's okay, because by the time
you get to go to sleep

15:11.734 --> 15:14.066
you really feel like
you've accomplished something

15:14.133 --> 15:17.767
for yourself and for your family.
It's a nice feeling.

15:18.467 --> 15:20.800
I guess that's what it feels
like to be grown up.

15:21.100 --> 15:22.033
Sometimes.

15:22.133 --> 15:23.367
[CHUCKLES]

15:23.433 --> 15:27.367
Hey, uh... What do you think
Matt's punishment should be?

15:27.600 --> 15:29.066
[CHUCKLES] What'd he do?

15:33.567 --> 15:35.533
Would you like to get
an ice cream with me?

15:36.166 --> 15:37.200
I'd love to.

15:42.266 --> 15:44.100
Good advice and ice cream?

15:44.166 --> 15:46.033
Maybe I should talk
to my dad more often.

15:46.767 --> 15:48.734
All I'm saying is
I just don't understand

15:48.800 --> 15:51.100
why you guys left
such an important decision up to me.

15:51.166 --> 15:52.367
I'm just a kid.

15:52.433 --> 15:53.500
Classic transference.

15:53.567 --> 15:55.433
He's our son, Howard
Let's not shrink him.

15:55.500 --> 15:57.767
But he's blaming me because
he didn't get Bar Mitzvah'd.

15:57.834 --> 15:59.333
-Oh, honey.
-Okay

15:59.400 --> 16:01.367
Parents are always the easiest target.

16:01.433 --> 16:03.633
It's just that you guys
tell me how to do everything--

16:03.700 --> 16:06.500
When to clean my room,
when to do my homework.

16:06.567 --> 16:08.200
When to clean my bellybutton for lint.

16:08.266 --> 16:09.700
Not true, not at all.

16:09.767 --> 16:12.266
Okay, maybe the last one,
but that's about hygiene.

16:12.333 --> 16:13.567
Sit down, David.

16:18.834 --> 16:19.934
[SIGHS]

16:20.266 --> 16:21.400
When you were six,

16:21.900 --> 16:24.633
and all the other kids
were taking the training wheels

16:24.700 --> 16:27.367
off their bikes,
you told me you weren't ready.

16:27.433 --> 16:29.100
I was made fun of, wasn't I?

16:29.667 --> 16:34.300
Yes, but that's not the point.
The point is you weren't ready.

16:34.367 --> 16:37.066
But now I feel like
I've missed out on something.

16:37.133 --> 16:40.200
My Bar Mitzvah should have
been a year ago. It's too late now.

16:40.367 --> 16:41.500
Why?

16:41.567 --> 16:43.734
I don't know.
'Cause I'm not 13 any more?

16:44.133 --> 16:45.433
You're not 13.

16:45.900 --> 16:48.667
But you've taken the time
to search, question,

16:48.734 --> 16:50.000
and talk to your peers.

16:50.066 --> 16:51.200
How do you know?

16:51.266 --> 16:52.266
Please, we're your parents.

16:52.333 --> 16:54.433
Like we're not going to see
every movie you make?

16:55.667 --> 16:57.567
David, trust yourself.

17:00.467 --> 17:01.533
[CHUCKLES]

17:01.600 --> 17:03.200
[SMACKS LIPS] I think I'm ready.

17:06.300 --> 17:07.300
Hey, Matt.

17:09.367 --> 17:13.333
Wow. You are really good
at this cleaning thing.

17:14.800 --> 17:16.266
Do I have a choice?

17:16.333 --> 17:18.433
It's the only punishment
Dad keeps going back to.

17:18.500 --> 17:19.734
What did you do this time?

17:20.266 --> 17:21.266
Overslept.

17:21.333 --> 17:22.934
What do you mean you overslept?

17:23.567 --> 17:25.166
I woke up late this morning.

17:25.233 --> 17:28.767
It was a total accident
but does Dad care? Nope.

17:28.834 --> 17:32.000
After this I have to mow the lawn
and wash the car.

17:32.066 --> 17:35.567
Whoa, whoa, whoa. All of that
just because you overslept?

17:35.633 --> 17:38.100
Yup. Watch your feet.

17:39.633 --> 17:42.133
Okay, okay, okay. Ha-ha, ha-ha. Stop.

17:42.934 --> 17:45.900
Matt. You must have done
something else.

17:45.967 --> 17:48.100
Did you... did you steal
more oranges or,

17:48.166 --> 17:49.834
or give more doggie haircuts?

17:49.967 --> 17:53.567
Nah. Dad's just really weird
when it comes to punishing me.

17:53.633 --> 17:56.333
I mean, I could do something
totally by accident, like,

17:56.400 --> 17:59.667
forget to flush the toilet
and he makes me sweep the chimney.

18:00.266 --> 18:02.133
Now, if I do something
on purpose like,

18:02.200 --> 18:04.934
let's say, cut Lizzie's hair
while she's sleeping...

18:05.000 --> 18:06.834
You cut your sister's hair?

18:06.900 --> 18:08.867
Hey-hey-hey, it's just a plan.

18:08.934 --> 18:11.200
I need to work out the finer points.

18:11.266 --> 18:15.500
Oh, my goodness, your father
has no idea how to do this job.

18:15.567 --> 18:18.200
Does that mean
you'll start punishing me again?

18:18.266 --> 18:20.667
'Cause... I kind of miss you, Mom.

18:20.734 --> 18:24.567
You do? Oh, honey, I miss you, too.

18:26.934 --> 18:28.433
Can I stop cleaning now?

18:28.500 --> 18:29.567
Yeah, of course you can.

18:31.500 --> 18:34.834
But because you told me your plan
about cutting your sister's hair,

18:34.900 --> 18:36.667
you're grounded until next week.

18:39.166 --> 18:41.433
It's great to be back
in business with you, Mom.

18:44.667 --> 18:46.033
You look great.

18:46.100 --> 18:47.567
Thanks, I wasn't sure what to wear.

18:47.633 --> 18:49.000
I've never been
to one of these before.

18:49.066 --> 18:50.567
-[CHUCKLES]
-Have you seen Gordo?

18:50.633 --> 18:52.100
He's probably inside.

18:52.166 --> 18:53.266
Think he's nervous?

18:53.333 --> 18:55.533
Knowing Gordo? Not a chance.

18:55.600 --> 18:57.400
I'm so proud of our Miranda.

18:57.500 --> 18:59.166
She's got such nice friends.

18:59.233 --> 19:00.834
[SMACKS LIPS]
Oh, you're just saying that

19:00.900 --> 19:02.834
because Gordo put you in his movie.

19:03.033 --> 19:04.400
No, really.

19:04.467 --> 19:06.300
-I know.
-[BOTH CHUCKLE]

19:06.367 --> 19:08.433
Come on.
I don't want to miss anything.

19:10.667 --> 19:14.467
Hey, Matt. Hold up.
Here. Straighten up your tie.

19:15.066 --> 19:16.133
Okay.

19:16.200 --> 19:17.567
It looked better before.

19:17.633 --> 19:19.633
Sorry, honey,
I think this is my job, too.

19:19.700 --> 19:21.900
Uh, don't I ever do anything right?

19:21.967 --> 19:23.600
-You make good pancakes.
-Thanks.

19:23.667 --> 19:25.166
And you picked me to be your wife.

19:25.233 --> 19:26.467
Mmm...

19:26.533 --> 19:28.000
I'll be going.

19:29.667 --> 19:31.333
Hey, let's go watch Gordo grow up.

19:31.400 --> 19:34.233
Wait. Just because Gordo is going
to be a man when this is all over,

19:34.300 --> 19:36.700
do you think things between us
are going to be different?

19:36.767 --> 19:38.734
Nah, I think he'll still be Gordo.
[CHUCKLES]

19:41.000 --> 19:42.900
Which is exactly the way I like him.

19:44.533 --> 19:46.233
Thank you all for coming
to my Bar Mitzvah.

19:47.166 --> 19:50.166
Today is important for a lot
of different reasons, but mostly,

19:50.233 --> 19:54.233
because today I leave my childhood
behind and become a man.

19:55.867 --> 19:58.600
Now, the truth is, I could have
marked this transition

19:58.667 --> 20:00.100
a million different ways

20:00.533 --> 20:02.433
and believe me,
I considered most of them.

20:07.000 --> 20:10.333
But I knew that whatever I did,
it had to be right for me.

20:12.066 --> 20:14.233
So I searched and I questioned

20:14.300 --> 20:16.433
and I heard lots of stories
from many men.

20:17.567 --> 20:22.000
Funny thing is, the person
I learned most about was me.

20:23.667 --> 20:26.300
And I realized that
figuring out who I am

20:26.367 --> 20:28.934
was made easier
by realizing who I'm not.

20:30.400 --> 20:34.367
So why this Bar Mitzvah
and not a tattoo?

20:34.433 --> 20:37.233
Or fishing? Or even a dirt bike?

20:38.967 --> 20:40.533
The answer is simple.

20:40.600 --> 20:42.834
It's because this is
what felt right to me.

21:01.100 --> 21:02.867
[PRAYING IN HEBREW]

21:27.533 --> 21:28.600
Those clothes are funny.

21:28.667 --> 21:30.200
MAN 1: And action.
MAN 2: What was that, Lalaine?

21:30.266 --> 21:33.200
MAN 3: And again, and again.
MAN 4: Here we go, guys, rolling.

21:34.967 --> 21:35.967
[CLATTERS]

21:36.033 --> 21:37.200
[GLASS SHATTERS]

21:37.600 --> 21:40.834
Elizabeth? Very funny, guys.

21:41.033 --> 21:42.066
All I'm saying is

21:42.133 --> 21:43.800
if they're going to go to the trouble
and remake... [LAUGHING]

21:44.166 --> 21:45.333
ADAM: Why are you laughing?

21:46.033 --> 21:48.300
[ALL LAUGHING]

21:49.033 --> 21:50.100
LALAINE: I'm sorry.

21:50.166 --> 21:52.400
JAKE: Whoo-hoo!
LALAINE: You're crazy, you're crazy.

21:54.700 --> 21:56.033
-[SNIFFLES]
-[GRUNTS]

21:57.233 --> 21:58.333
I love you.

21:59.233 --> 22:02.300
-I have feelings for you, too.
-[LAUGHTER]

22:03.467 --> 22:05.467
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
